                "list": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "List",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p><strong>BPA Plastics</strong> — No plastic touches your water at any stage — not in the housing, not in the cartridge shell, not in the seals.</p><p><strong>Painted or Coated Finishes</strong> — Coatings chip, wear, and eventually flake into the water they're meant to protect. We finish in raw, hand-brushed metal instead.</p><p><strong>Adhesive Seals</strong> — Glue degrades under repeated moisture and heat cycling. Every seal in a HAUSTAS system is mechanical, not chemical.</p><p><strong>Disposable Components</strong> — If a part can wear out, it's designed to be replaced on its own — not to force you to throw away the whole system.</p>",
